As part of the efforts by the Lagos State University to create awareness on the ongoing coronavirus pandemic, the institutionâ€™s Department of Computer Science has developed a mobile App that will enable individuals to do a self-test for the disease. Prof. Benjamin Aribisala led the team that developed the App. Other team members include Dr. Oluwatoyin Enikuomehin, Mr. Olusola Olabanjo, Abdulazeez Saheed and Dr. Abdulazeez Anjorin of theMicrobiology Department. The software, which has been tested and certified by the Provost Lagos State University College of Medicine, Ikeja, will be available on Playstore from April 7, 2020. 